article.headline: No. 2 North Carolina 105, Ark.-Pine Bluff 49
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. --  Cetera DeGraffenreid scored 19 points and No. 2 North Carolina routed Arkansas-Pine Bluff 105-49 on Monday night.

She'la White had 17 points and Chay Shegog added 15 -- both career highs -- for the Tar Heels (11-0), while Jessica Breland added 10.

North Carolina, which shot 53.3 percent from the field and forced 36 turnovers, has won 74 consecutive nonconference home games.

Rashanda McCants, North Carolina's second-leading scorer, dressed but didn't play because of a sprained finger on her right hand.

Ciara Shields and Jonae Prince-Coleman both had nine points for the Lady Lions (1-6), whose leading scorer, Arica Green with a 16.0 average, was held to two points.

The Tar Heels got 13 first-half points from Shegog on 5-of-6 shooting to take a 52-27 lead. They used a 22-0 run to go up 70-29 early in the second half.
